events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Jordan Jefferson passed for a career-high 254 yards, threw for one touchdown and ran for another, and LSU survived a thrilling upset bid by Mississippi 43-36 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: LSU survives Ole Miss

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Andrew Luck threw two touchdown passes and led Stanford to scores on all eight possessions he played as the Cardinal beat California 48-14 Saturday for its most lopsided win in the Big Game in 80 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford trucks Cal

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Montee Ball and James White combined for 354 yards rushing and six touchdowns, leading Wisconsin one step closer to its first Big Ten championship since 1999 with a a 48-28 win at Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin rolls; Robinson sets records

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Cyrus Gray ran for a career-high tying 137 yards and Randy Bullock kicked the go-ahead field goal with about three minutes left as No. 18 Texas A&M knocked off ninth-ranked Nebraska 9-6 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M rolls on, tripping Nebraska

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Dan Herron rushed for a 1-yard touchdown with 1:47 left and Ohio State rallied to beat Iowa 20-17 Saturday to keep its hopes for a Rose Bowl bid alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio St. holds off Iowa

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden passed for 389 yards and three touchdowns to lead Oklahoma State to a share of the Big 12 South title with a 48-14 win over Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Okla. St. grabs share of Big 12 South

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins lunged into the end zone from 3 yards out with 4:32 remaining, and Michigan State kept its Rose Bowl hopes alive with a dramatic 35-31 victory over Purdue on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spartans' Cousins spoils upset bid by Purdue

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Ryan Mallett threw for 306 yards and three touchdowns, including the game-winner to Knile Davis in double overtime, and No. 13 Arkansas beat Mississippi State 38-31 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 Arkansas fights off Miss. State in 2OT

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: DeMarco Murray turned a short pass into a long touchdown and ran for another score in the opening minutes to get 16th-ranked Oklahoma off to a fast start in a 53-24 victory over Baylor on Saturday night that kept the Sooners' Big 12 title hopes alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: OU blasts Baylor, keeps Big 12 title hopes afloat

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Blaine Gabbert threw a touchdown pass and No. 15 Missouri turned a fake punt into another score in a 14-0 victory over Iowa State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gabbert, No. 15 Missouri sneak past Iowa State

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Ryan Williams ran for 142 yards and two touchdowns, including a career-long 84-yarder in the fourth quarter, and Virginia Tech beat Miami 31-17 on Saturday to win the Atlantic Coast Conference's Coastal Division title.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech in ACC title game

events.name: Troy Trojans at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Marcus Lattimore had three touchdowns and 102 yards rushing by halftime and South Carolina scored its most points under coach Steve Spurrier, routing Troy 69-24 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lattimore, South Carolina run wild over Troy

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Nevada Wolf Pack

headlines.description: Vai Taua ran for 111 yards and two touchdowns and scored a third on a 79-yard pass Saturday to lead Nevada past New Mexico State 52-6.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nevada secures 1st 10-win season since 1991

events.name: Utah Utes at San Diego State Aztecs

headlines.description: Jordan Wynn threw for a career-high 362 yards and Greg Bird's blocked punt set up the go-ahead score for No. 25 Utah in a 38-34 win over San Diego State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wynn's career night lifts No. 23 Utah past SDSU

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Christian Ponder threw for 170 yards and a touchdown, and Florida State beat Maryland 30-16 Saturday night to remain in the hunt to play in the Atlantic Coast Conference title game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Noles hang on as Terps throw away ACC hopes

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Dion Lewis rushed for 105 yards and a touchdown Saturday, helping Pittsburgh beat South Florida 17-10 to retain sole possession of first place in the Big East.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pittsburgh tops USF to keep lead in Big East

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Matt McGloin threw for 315 yards and two scores, James Van Fleet returned a blocked punt for a touchdown, and Penn State found the nation's capital to be a satisfactory home away from home as they beat Indiana 41-24.
headlines.shortLinkText: McGloin too much as Penn St. handles Indiana

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: West Virginia kept its hopes for a Big East title alive with a rugged 17-10 win over Louisville on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: WVU keeps Big East title hopes alive

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Montel Harris carried 24 times for 114 yards, including a go-ahead 4-yard touchdown late in the third quarter, to lift surging Boston College to bowl eligibility with a 17-13 victory over slumping Virginia on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris carries bowl-eligible BC past Virginia

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Owen Spencer caught a tipped ball in the end zone for a touchdown on fourth down and T.J. Graham returned a punt 87 yards for another score to help North Carolina State rally past rival North Carolina 29-25 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State edges UNC on late highlight-reel plays

headlines.shortLinkText: James Madison 14, Maine 10

headlines.description: Chad Spann rushed for three touchdowns and Northern Illinois clinched at least share of the Mid-American West Division title.
headlines.shortLinkText: NIU routs Ball State, clinches MAC West title

events.name: Appalachian State Mountaineers at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jordan Reed accounted for four touchdowns, including a pass to quarterback John Brantley, and Florida beat Appalachian State 48-10 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Appalachian St. falls to Florida's sudden offense

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Mario Butler returned an interception 85 yards for a touchdown, Tevin Washington threw a 79-yard scoring pass to Stephen Hill and Georgia Tech beat Duke 30-20 on Saturday to ensure eligibility for its 14th straight bowl appearance.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia Tech bowl eligible after win over Duke

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Kyle Parker threw two touchdown passes, Jamie Harper rushed for 142 yards and Clemson beat Wake Forest 30-10 on Saturday.

headlines.shortLinkText: SMU beats Marshall to become bowl eligible

events.name: Weber State Wildcats at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Taylor Potts threw for three touchdowns and ran for another -- all in the first half -- to lead Texas Tech over Weber State 64-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas Tech rips Weber St., earns bowl eligibility

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Mikel Leshoure ran for a school-record 330 yards and two touchdowns, and Illinois beat Northwestern 48-27 Saturday in a game played under circumstances at Wrigley Field.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois corners Northwestern in Wrigley rout

headlines.description: Tyler Eifert caught a touchdown pass a few steps away from the home dugout, Darrin Walls returned an interception 42 yards for a score and Notre Dame beat Army 27-3 Saturday night in the first football game at the new Yankee Stadium.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notre Dame batters Army in Yankee Stadium

events.name: Connecticut Huskies at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Jordan Todman ran for 130 yards and scored on two short runs, and Connecticut capitalized on two turnovers to beat Syracuse 23-6 on Saturday night.

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Tauren Poole rushed for 99 yards and the game-clinching touchdown and Tennessee kept its slim bowl hopes alive under first-year coach Derek Dooley with a lackluster 20-10 win over Vanderbilt on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tennessee ekes past Vandy to stay in bowl hunt

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Cincinnati's offense put together a bevy of big plays on Saturday night, beating Rutgers 69-38 in the highest-scoring game in Big East history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pead's 5 TD passes power Cincy past Rutgers

events.name: USC Trojans at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Ryan Katz threw for 154 yards and two touchdowns while Jacquizz Rodgers rushed for 128 yards and another score, and Oregon State defeated No. 20 Southern California 36-7 Saturday night.
